## Monorepo layout

```
<%= projectName %>/
├── package.json                # Root devDependencies (create-stackr for the `stackr` CLI)
├── stackr.config.json          # Source of truth for services, orm, ports
├── docker-compose.yml          # Managed by stackr (marker blocks)
├── docker-compose.prod.yml     # Production overlay
├── scripts/
│   ├── setup.mjs               # `<%= packageManager %> run setup` — loops services, installs deps, wires stackr CLI
│   ├── test-all.mjs            # `<%= packageManager %> run test` — component + unit across backends
│   └── test-e2e.mjs            # `<%= packageManager %> run test:e2e` — cross-service E2E
<% services.forEach((svc) => { -%>
├── <%= svc.name %>/
│   ├── backend/
<% if (svc.web && svc.web.enabled) { -%>
│   ├── web/
<% } -%>
<% if (svc.mobile && svc.mobile.enabled) { -%>
│   ├── mobile/
<% } -%>
<% }); -%>
```

## Architecture

Each service has its own isolated Postgres database and Redis cache.
Non-auth services verify requests by forwarding cookies to
`${AUTH_SERVICE_URL}/api/auth/get-session`. See `DESIGN.md` and each
service's own `backend/DESIGN.md` for the full picture.

## Adding a service later

The root `package.json` pins `create-stackr` as a devDependency, so
after `<%= packageManager %> run setup` finishes the root install the
`stackr` CLI is available locally. To grow the monorepo without
clobbering your docker-compose edits:

```bash
npx stackr add service wallet
# or: <%= packageManager %> run stackr -- add service wallet
```

If you'd rather have `stackr` on your PATH system-wide, install it
globally once:

```bash
npm i -g create-stackr
stackr add service wallet
```

Either way, `stackr.config.json` stays the source of truth for the
monorepo shape.
